        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-11-05 18:14:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified-1\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.5/x86_64: (https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/33cd3a62-6512-11e4-ab6d-5254006e85c2).  Ran 13 tests.  2 tests failed: sanity-lfsck, sanity-quota.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fe06200569cfec78e4a0ef1196d6829d8deac55b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-11-05 18:41:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> ccc_internal.h shouldn't exist. I'd like to dump everything in it to vvp_internal.h.\n\nOK but that takes a lot more than the current patch set does. With the current set applied: llite_internal.h depends on ccc_internal.h; vvp_internal.h depends on llite_internal.h; some of the vvp structures are defined in llite_internal.h; so some of the vvp_*.c files depend on llite_internal.h.\n\nIt can all be sorted out but some llite internal layering needs to be defined to do so. For example, should the definition of vvp_io go in vvp_internal.h? If so then is it OK that file.c includes vvp_internal.h?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "9e50fa4afb99a57dde009f5578c8bcfea9863863",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-11-05 19:20:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n\"It can all be sorted out but some llite internal layering needs to be defined to do so. For example, should the definition of vvp_io go in vvp_internal.h? If so then is it OK that file.c includes vvp_internal.h?\"\n\nIdeally llite_internal.h should only include legacy code and anything else directly related to CLIO should be moved to vvp_internal.h.\n\nHow much work will it be to just move everything in lclient.h to vvp_internal.h and sort out dependencies, but don't change any symbol names?\n\nAnyway, the most important thing is to get rid of lclient.h and anything else is secondary.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "4feaabc5898f5323f36f8e5e29d5b92d5bc0144b",
      "author": {
